<TITLE> Former Fed chief says US economic growth slowing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Former Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan said on Sunday the rate of US economic growth was slowing, but that the odds of a recession are less than 50 percent. Greenspan also said in an interview with CNN's "Late Edition with Wolf Blitzer" that the turmoil caused by the subprime mortgage crisis was easing and financial markets were beginning to go back to normal.
